      "body" : "> Concept ACK to unifying types for transaction sizes. But if we're going to do this, why use a signed type? We don't have negative sizes, do we?\r\n\r\nThe rule of thumb is to use signed types for anything that involves arithmetic operations (addition or subtraction). Obviously the standard library doesn't make that easy with `size_t` being unsigned.",
